r />\n<br />\nWhen I first shot Kokerbooms under the Milky Way in Keetmanshoop in Southern Namibia, they were lit up by flood light at the compound in which I was staying. I then travelled far off into the countryside and shot them in pitch blackness.<br />\n<br />\nAfter we reviewing the shots, I ended up liking some of these lit-up shots. It reminds me of some sort of alien invasion or something like The Day of the Triffids.<br />\n<br />\n<b>-------</b><br />\n<br />\n<b>No images in comments please.</b><br />\n<br />\n<b>Details</b><br />\n<i>Nikon D800 / ISO 1600 / f/2.8 / 25s / Nikkor 14-24mm f/2.8G ED @ 14mm / Location: Keetmanshoop, Namibia</i></p>\";s:15:\"description_raw\";s:989:\"<b><a href=\"http://thefella.com\" rel=\"nofollow\">TheFella</a> | <a href=\"http://f8.pe\" rel=\"nofollow\">f/8 Photo Expeditions</a> | <a href=\"http://www.instagram.com/thefella\" rel=\"nofollow\">Instagram</a> | <a href=\"http://www.facebook.com/thefella\" rel=\"nofollow\">Facebook</a></b>\n\n<b>-------</b>\n\n<b><a href=\"https://thefella.com/photo/the-invasion\" rel=\"nofollow\">thefella.com/photo/the-invasion</a></b> \n\nWhen I first shot Kokerbooms under the Milky Way in Keetmanshoop in Southern Namibia, they were lit up by flood light at the compound in which I was staying. I then travelled far off into the countryside and shot them in pitch blackness.\n\nAfter we reviewing the shots, I ended up liking some of these lit-up shots. It reminds me of some sort of alien invasion or something like The Day of the Triffids.\n\n<b>-------</b>\n\n<b>No images in comments please.</b>\n\n<b>Details</b>\n<i>Nikon D800 / ISO 1600 / f/2.8 / 25s / Nikkor 14-24mm f/2.8G ED @ 14mm / Location: Keetmanshoop, Namibia</i>\";s:5:\"m_url\";s:62:\"https://live.staticflickr.com/460/19375724632_53bf1945b1_m.jpg\";s:5:\"t_url\";s:62:\"https://live.staticflickr.com/460/19375724632_53bf1945b1_s.jpg\";s:5:\"l_url\";s:60:\"https://live.staticflickr.com/460/19375724632_53bf1945b1.jpg\";s:9:\"photo_xml\"